   <p/> The Bonnethead Shark(Sphyrna tiburo) is a fish from the hammerheads family (Sphyrnidae), order of predator sharks (Carcharhiniformes), that lives in the Pacific and the Atlantic Ocean.
<p/>The Bonnethead Shark can reach the maximum length of 150 cm. The body has a streched form.
<p/>The fish has no sideline.
<p/>The Bonnethead Shark lives in salt and brakish water in a subtropic climate. The depth of the water is about 10 to 80 cm. from the surface.
<p/>It feeds on fish, buy hunting small fish. (it is a predator fish)
<p/>The Bonnethead Shark is of great importance for commercial fishing. This shark is also hunted by fishers.

